</table>
<ol>
<li>Voiceless plosives are lightly <a href="/wiki/Aspiration_(phonetics)" title="Aspiration (phonetics)">aspirated</a> but unreleased before another consonant.<sup id="cite_ref-Harvcoltxt.7CTench.7C2007.7Cp.3D229_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Harvcoltxt.7CTench.7C2007.7Cp.3D229-2"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
<li><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/t/</span> and <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/d/</span> formally had <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/tʃ/</span> and <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/dʒ/</span> respectively as allophones but the two pairs have split; however, the alveolar plosives never precede front vowels and the postalveolar affricates rarely precede anything but front vowels.<sup id="cite_ref-Harvcoltxt.7CTench.7C2007.7Cp.3D229_2-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Harvcoltxt.7CTench.7C2007.7Cp.3D229-2"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
<li><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/h/</span> is a relatively new phoneme, appearing in loanwords from <a href="/wiki/English_language" title="English language">English</a> and <a href="/wiki/Hausa_language" title="Hausa language">Hausa</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-Harvcoltxt.7CTench.7C2007.7Cp.3D229_2-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Harvcoltxt.7CTench.7C2007.7Cp.3D229-2"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
<li><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/jˀ/</span> derives from a <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/ɗʲ/</span> that has lost its alveolar contact while retaining the palatal and glottal action.<sup id="cite_ref-Harvcoltxt.7CTench.7C2007.7Cp.3D229_2-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Harvcoltxt.7CTench.7C2007.7Cp.3D229-2"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></li>
</ol>
<table class="wikitable" style="text-align: center;">
